Rating: 4
Scrumptious! I doubled the apple filling but only used 1 stick butter total (i.e., 1/2 stick doubled). I also doubled the shortbread base but substituted 1/2 cup of the doubled flour with cornstarch, for extra silkiness. I then used half of that as the actual base and the other half as the topping, instead of using any bread crumbs. Because of all the extra filling it had to bake for about an hour and 15 minutes. It came out perfectly, kind of like a rectangular apple pie with a coffee-cake-type crumb topping. The doubled filling more or less filled the whole pan but didn't spill over when cooking. I let it sit for a couple of hours before serving. Refrigerated leftovers were equally delicious cold, but a bit more difficult to get out of the pan. Yum!

