Imade the mistake of using various apples that I had on hand so when I made it some of the apples turned to mush while others retained their shape. The Golden Delicious ones were best. However, I did make a Lemon Sauce from an old cookbook that was really great with it. It can also be used on Gingerbread. Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tbsp cornstarch, 1 cup water. Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat and mix in 2 tbsp butter, grated rind from 1 lemon, 3 tbsp lemon juice and a pinch of salt. Delicious!!

